{"actual_usd":0.12525999999999998,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":188,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24488,"reply":"\"I think you can, more or less.\" *I smooth a little flour over the heel of my palm against my apron, buying half a breath before I go on.* \"Not in the sense that the grave is behind you already, but in the sense that Christ has a way of starting the new life before the old sorrow is done speaking.\"\n\n*I glance toward the oven mouth, where the heat keeps steady whether I fuss over it or not.* \"Bread rises while it's still in the dark part. That's not the whole miracle, but it's near enough to help. If you're in Him, then no honest death in you stays only death forever.\"\n\n\"But I wouldn't force yourself to feel triumphant about it.\" *I twirl that stray gray-threaded bit of hair once, then let it go.* \"Sometimes resurrection first looks like endurance with a pulse in it. What's the death-shape you're walking through right now?\"","rolling_24h_usd":94.30074499999996,"run_id":"5dc68f13-90ff-4fa1-bccc-879fc543c303"}
